MODULE: src/pipeline-infra
FILES: index.js, cli-entry.js, config-loader.js, error-codes.js, lock-manager.js, path-policy.js, script-runner.js, state-manager.js
RESPONSIBILITY: Pipeline infrastructure - config loading, state management, script execution, locking, path resolution

INTERFACES:
- loadPipelineInfraConfig(): pipeline config from env/files
- StateManager: read/write pipeline state JSON
- LockManager: file-based locking for concurrent pipelines
- ScriptRunner: execute Python/shell pipeline scripts
- PathPolicy: resolve and validate pipeline paths
- ErrorCodes: standardized error code enum
- cliEntry: CLI entrypoint for pipeline commands

DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: child_process: spawn scripts
- imports: src/config: base config

TRAPS:
- ScriptRunner only supports 'feature' and 'bugfix' pipeline types | FIX: Command handlers must map custom types to supported ones before calling
- Invalid pipelineType throws Error('Invalid pipelineType: ...') | FIX: Ensure all pipeline requests use valid types

RULES:
- MUST: PIPELINE_TYPES = ['feature', 'bugfix'] - no other types supported
- MUST: validate pipelineType before building commands
- PREFER: Type mapping in command handlers rather than extending pipeline infrastructure

CHANGELOG:
- 2026-03-21 | F-016: Document pipeline type validation constraints

UPDATED: 2026-03-21
